#: ../../../user/quickstart.rst:1453
msgid "Histograms"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/quickstart.rst:1455
msgid ""
"The NumPy ``histogram`` function applied to an array returns a pair of "
"vectors: the histogram of the array and a vector of the bin edges. Beware: "
"``matplotlib`` also has a function to build histograms (called ``hist``, as "
"in Matlab) that differs from the one in NumPy. The main difference is that "
"``pylab.hist`` plots the histogram automatically, while ``numpy.histogram`` "
"only generates the data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/quickstart.rst:1477
msgid "With Matplotlib >=3.4 you can also use ``plt.stairs(n, bins)``."
msgstr ""

